{"TopicId":36137,"ForumId":18,"TopicTitle":"What\u0026#039;s your favourite \u0026quot;old\u0026quot; game?","CreatedByName":"joppiesaus","CreatedById":57698,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-07-06T18:27:12Z","PageNum":16,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"ExplodingRocketShips","CreatedById":85454,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-12T17:55:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003ETeam Fortress 2, Which, for the record, came out in 2007.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI also like Hot Wheels: Velocity X on the PS2, from the far-off past of 2002.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sonny_Jim","CreatedById":103060,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-12T18:15:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EJeez, this thread is making me feel mega-old. I mean, talking about games made in the 2000\u0027s and calling them old?\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E/me strokes pinball table.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Denks","CreatedById":135741,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-12T20:08:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EZoo Tycoon and Roller Coaster Tycoon are the best. I spent a ton of time on those games.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Special Agent Sigvan","CreatedById":92033,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-12T20:22:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EMount \u0026amp; Blade\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MiltiTrace","CreatedById":99150,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-12T20:55:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003ENot my favorite, but in Fragile allegiance (1997) you can move asteroids and use them as weapon)\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Ciframe width=\u0022459\u0022 height=\u0022344\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/nMx0Z8PCk2k?feature=oembed\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cp\u003Ealso Crusader: no regret\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Ciframe width=\u0022459\u0022 height=\u0022344\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/sdd9o9YpNB0?feature=oembed\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"bdito","CreatedById":112760,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-12T21:00:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/2/28/BaseballStarsNESCover.jpg/265px-BaseballStarsNESCover.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022265px-BaseballStarsNESCover.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:8px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#C0C0C0;\u0022\u003E- - - Updated - - -\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022MiltiTrace\u0022 data-cite=\u0022MiltiTrace\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Cp\u003Ealso Crusader: no regret\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI loved that game. I could never remember what its name was though. Now I do \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ouion","CreatedById":38531,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-13T00:39:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EMy favorite old games is RollerCoaster Tycoon 3 and R-Type Command( I wish R-type Command 2 is out in North America)\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/a/a7/RTC3-cover_art.png\u0022 alt=\u0022RTC3-cover_art.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/3/3c/R-Type_Command_Coverart.png\u0022 alt=\u0022R-Type_Command_Coverart.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bill Phil","CreatedById":127797,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-13T01:01:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EMegaman II.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ENothong beats the blue bomber!\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"xcorps","CreatedById":96531,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-13T02:05:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EYars Revenge (atari 2600)\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EXcom \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EHarpoon (seriously, has a more complete game ever been made?)\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Beowolf","CreatedById":48927,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-16T03:17:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022xcorps\u0022 data-cite=\u0022xcorps\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EHarpoon (seriously, has a more complete game ever been made?)\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI still have a copy I play sometimes.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Special Agent Sigvan","CreatedById":92033,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-16T05:24:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI lied.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIt\u0027s XCOM-UFO Defense.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIf you can get past the art style (Which is kinda trash), it\u0027s amazing.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"moogoob","CreatedById":118251,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-16T17:00:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EDoom. Nothing more relaxing than an Ultra-violence run of Episode 3. \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Plusk","CreatedById":103195,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-16T19:05:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EFallout 2. \u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:8px;\u0022\u003E12 more chars.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sal_vager","CreatedById":16426,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-16T19:11:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003Echaracter limit is 5 now, so I could say my favourite old game is DOOM! \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-16T19:16:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EDoom2\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:8px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#C0C0C0;\u0022\u003E- - - Updated - - -\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThat was just to test. But Doom2 was the first game I bought for PC, as I bought it with my first PC ever in late 1993. Before that it was an Apple and a Timex Sinclair 1000 \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn that Apple I had the original Elite which is still one of my favorites ever, as well.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ECan I also say Adventure on ATARI? That was a great. Still fun today if you can find the ports and clones that have been cobbled together over the years. I have particularly fond memories of Indenture.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MartGonzo","CreatedById":65764,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-16T19:37:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022moogoob\u0022 data-cite=\u0022moogoob\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EDoom. Nothing more relaxing than an Ultra-violence run of Episode 3. \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022sal_vager\u0022 data-cite=\u0022sal_vager\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003Echaracter limit is 5 now, so I could say my favourite old game is DOOM! \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u00225thHorseman\u0022 data-cite=\u00225thHorseman\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003EDoom2\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIf you still have a copy, give this a try, you won\u0027t regret it \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.moddb.com/mods/brutal-doom\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://www.moddb.com/mods/brutal-doom\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003Eplus this will make it even better\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.moddb.com/mods/brutal-doom/addons/ultimate-doom-i-and-ii-metal-rededited\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://www.moddb.com/mods/brutal-doom/addons/ultimate-doom-i-and-ii-metal-rededited\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Panzerbeard","CreatedById":66380,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-16T22:38:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI love so many older games that I really couldn\u0027t choose a favourite. The one I happen to be playing at the moment, though:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/odlx08E.png\u0022 alt=\u0022odlx08E.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI wanted to push my 550Ti to the limit. Look at all those pixels! So many pixels!\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe game is The Longest Journey, incase you don\u0027t recognise it. Fantastic point \u0026amp; click that I never got around to completing, since I was about 7 when I played it \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ethanadams","CreatedById":136913,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-18T15:34:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EGalactica,\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222015-02-18T19:26:36Z\u0022 title=\u002202/18/2015 07:26  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00229 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 18, 2015\u003C/time\u003E by Ethanadams\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Pixel of Life","CreatedById":45646,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-18T17:46:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003ENeed For Speed II SE, NFS Hot Pursuit 2, NFS Underground 2 and the original NFS Most Wanted from 2005. A-freaking-mazing. They don\u0027t make \u0027em the way they used to anymore.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cydonian Monk","CreatedById":69224,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-18T18:20:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EEmperor of the Fading Suns. (EFS) The game is 20 years old at this point, but I still break it out on occasion. Hex-based strategy game on a galactic scale. Fallen humanity rising from the ashes. Tech that can be learned and lost and learned again. Aliens, priests, nobles and merchants, all trying to get the advantage. Nowhere near as much fun single player as it was in Play-By-Email. It was the off-board, out-of-game political posturing that made the game great. And the soundtrack. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EGuess I\u0027ll add Darklands and the original X-Com to my list as runners up.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Souper","CreatedById":86003,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-18T19:54:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Noctis\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EThis one,\u003C/a\u003E even though I\u0027ve only recently discovered it, it was created around back in the MS-DOS period, making it ancient. It\u0027s awesome. Sad to see it\u0027s vaporware, and is probably dead fore ever or until someone else picks up on it.\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Othuyeg","CreatedById":105454,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-18T20:09:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EDuke Nukem 3D\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EStar Control 2\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Hrv123","CreatedById":129135,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-18T21:26:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022https://www.mobygames.com//images/shots/l/282895-sid-meier-s-pirates-amiga-screenshot-meeting-with-the-governor.png\u0022 alt=\u0022282895-sid-meier-s-pirates-amiga-screenshot-meeting-with-the-governor.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EPirates, Amiga version\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Newt","CreatedById":131025,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-18T23:38:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EMyst. I like Myst.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2015-02-19T04:53:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI liked the idea of Emperor of the Fading Suns, but the AI opposition was practically inert, so I didn\u0027t play it much. The game, that is. I \u003Cem\u003Elove \u003C/em\u003Ethe soundtrack music and still play it. \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}